  "notes": [
    {
      "title": "The Feminine Far Demonstrative تِلْكَ",
      "titleArabic": "اسم الإشارة للبعيد المؤنث",
      "content": [
        "تِلْكَ (tilka) is the feminine equivalent of ذَلِكَ, meaning 'that' for feminine nouns that are far away.",
        "Now you know all four demonstratives: هَذَا (this, masc.), ذَلِكَ (that, masc.), هَذِهِ (this, fem.), and تِلْكَ (that, fem.)."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "تِلْكَ is 'that' for feminine singular nouns",
        "Use هَذِهِ for near feminine nouns, تِلْكَ for far feminine nouns",
        "Place nouns like مَدْرَسَةٌ (school) and جَامِعَةٌ (university) are feminine"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "تِلْكَ مَدْرَسَةٌ", "english": "That is a school" },
        { "arabic": "تِلْكَ جَامِعَةٌ", "english": "That is a university" },
        { "arabic": "هَذِهِ غُرْفَةٌ وَتِلْكَ نَافِذَةٌ", "english": "This is a room and that is a window" },
        { "arabic": "هَذِهِ آمِنَةُ وَتِلْكَ مَرْيَمُ", "english": "This is Aminah and that is Maryam" }
      ]
    }
  ],
